Title: EXTERIOR PANELS / TRIM: FRONT BUMPER: REASSEMBLY; 2021 - 2022 MY Prius [07/2020 -        ]

REASSEMBLY

PROCEDURE

1. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER SIDE SUPPORT LH

(a) Engage the claw as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(b) Engage the clip as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(c) Install the front bumper side support LH with the bolt.

Torque:

12.5 N·m {127 kgf·cm, 9 ft·lbf}

2. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER SIDE SUPPORT RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

3. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION LH

(a) Install the front bumper extension LH with the 4 bolts.

Torque:

12 N·m {122 kgf·cm, 9 ft·lbf}

4. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

5. INSTALL NO. 2 FRONT BUMPER REINFORCEMENT

(a) Install the No. 2 front bumper reinforcement with the 4 nuts.

Torque:

30 N·m {306 kgf·cm, 22 ft·lbf}

6. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER REINFORCEMENT SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Engage the 2 guides.

(b) Install the front bumper reinforcement sub-assembly with the 8 bolts.

Torque:

50 N·m {510 kgf·cm, 37 ft·lbf}

(c) Engage the 7 clamps.

7. INSTALL RADIATOR SHUTTER SUB-ASSEMBLY

Click here

8. INSTALL THERMISTOR ASSEMBLY

Click here

9. INSTALL LOWER FRONT BUMPER ABSORBER

(a) Install the lower front bumper absorber with the 3 clips.

10. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER ENERGY ABSORBER

(a) Engage the 4 guides to install the front bumper energy absorber as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

11. INSTALL NO. 2 FRONT BUMPER PAD

HINT:

When installing the No. 2 front bumper pad, heat the front bumper cover using a heat light.

Heating Temperature

Item

Temperature

Front Bumper Cover

40 to 60°C (104 to 140°F)

CAUTION:

  • Do not touch the heat light and heated parts, touching the heat light may result in burns.
  • Touching heated parts for a long time may result in burns.

*a

Heated Part

*b

Heat Light

NOTICE:

Do not heat the front bumper cover excessively.

(a) Clean the front bumper cover surface.

(1) Using a heat light, heat the front bumper cover surface.

(2) Remove any remaining double-sided tape from the front bumper cover.

(3) Wipe off any tape adhesive residue with cleaner.

(b) Remove the release paper from a new No. 2 front bumper pad.

HINT:

After removing the release paper, keep the exposed adhesive free from foreign matter.

(c) Install the No. 2 front bumper pad.

HINT:

Press the No. 2 front bumper pad firmly to install it.

12. INSTALL NO. 1 FRONT BUMPER PAD

HINT:

When installing the No. 1 front bumper pad, heat the front bumper cover using a heat light.

Heating Temperature

Item

Temperature

Front Bumper Cover

40 to 60°C (104 to 140°F)

CAUTION:

  • Do not touch the heat light and heated parts, touching the heat light may result in burns.
  • Touching heated parts for a long time may result in burns.

*a

Heated Part

*b

Heat Light

NOTICE:

Do not heat the front bumper cover excessively.

(a) Clean the front bumper cover surface.

(1) Using a heat light, heat the front bumper cover surface.

(2) Remove any remaining double-sided tape from the front bumper cover.

(3) Wipe off any tape adhesive residue with cleaner.

(b) Remove the release paper from a new No. 1 front bumper pad.

HINT:

After removing the release paper, keep the exposed adhesive free from foreign matter.

(c) Install the No. 1 front bumper pad.

HINT:

  • Press the No. 1 front bumper pad firmly to install it.
  • Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

19. INSTALL HOOD TO FRONT END PANEL SEAL

(a) Remove the release paper from a new hood to front end panel seal.

HINT:

After removing the release paper, keep the exposed adhesive free from foreign matter.

(b) Engage the 2 clips and attach the double-sided tape to install the hood to front end panel seal.
